headline: Tractor Supply (TSCO) Expands Equine Range With Exclusive SmartEquine Partnership
summary: Tractor Supply (TSCO) has been making headlines with its recent partnership with SmartEquine, launching SmartPaks supplements, which may have supported its share price increase of 17% over the past quarter. The enhancement of its product lineup demonstrates TSCO's dedication to addressing equine health and wellness needs. Meanwhile, the company's solid quarterly earnings reflect strong sales figures, though its net income for the first half of 2025 saw a decrease. Despite these mixed earnings...

headline: Tractor Supply Bolsters Support of Farmer Veterans With $100,000 Donation
summary: BRENTWOOD, Tenn., July 29, 2025--Tractor Supply Company (NASDAQ: TSCO), the largest rural lifestyle retailer in the United States, and the Tractor Supply Company Foundation announced today they have made a $100,000 donation to the Farmer Veteran Coalition’s (FVC) Fellowship Fund, which provides micro grants to veterans in their beginning years of farming or ranching. content.summary: BRENTWOOD, Tenn., July 29, 2025--Tractor Supply Company (NASDAQ: TSCO), the largest rural lifestyle retailer in the United States, and the Tractor Supply Company Foundation announced today they have made a $100,000 donation to the Farmer Veteran Coalition’s (FVC) Fellowship Fund, which provides micro grants to veterans in their beginning years of farming or ranching. This marks the seventh year Tractor Supply has partnered with FVC to assist farmer veterans as part of its ongoing commitment to H

thumbnail.caption: Army veteran and Farmer Veteran Coalition (FVC) member Phil Rosso and his grandson, Kayden, accept a gift card from Audrey Rassel, Store Manager of the Cleveland, Georgia, Tractor Supply. Phil is one of 50 veterans from all branches of the U.S. Military to each receive a $1,000 Tractor Supply gift card to purchase items that will make a crucial difference in their farm businesses. FVC received $100,000 as part of Tractor Supply’s $1 million contribution to charities that support the Company’s Hometown Heroes program.
